The paper deals with learning compact yet discriminative patch descriptors within a deep learning framework, which is a common problem in computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves a convolutional network framework for learning binary patch descriptors, which falls under the category of machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The paper also experiments with matching patches from different datasets, which involves multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR) techniques.
